{
  "stem": "33.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You have a big oral and written examination-- not only with your teachers but with a committee that comes from other schools and the Board of Education.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Usually, the president of the Board of Education is all of these committees.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The five of us-- the seven of us Jews, actually-- the two boys, too-- were allowed to take-- our written exams were already finished.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we took our oral exams earlier as a separate group, because we had to go into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was May the 1st, of 1944, when we had our oral examinations.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The ghetto started on May the 3rd of 1944, on my 18th birthday.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We didn't know about it until it started.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But that morning, I remember our rabbi Sunday school teacher, a young man, probably under 30 at that time, Dr.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Alexander Hertzog, came to pick us up, because he was put in charge of registering people for the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So the handful of Jewish students, a handful of us that were still going to school and a few who already graduated high school a year before or a couple of years before, we went with him.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we helped him with the-- the registering of the people who came into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "As I said, it started on May the 3rd.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Our turn came probably close to two weeks later, about the last people to get into this area.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We lived the opposite side of the town from the ghetto area.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The ghetto area was actually a very heavily Jewish-- Jewish populated area before, but there were some non-Jews there too who were evacuated.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was about a three square block area.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
